  "response": "To recover your Gmail password using a recovery mobile number and Gmail address, follow these steps:\n\n1. Go to the Google Sign-In page\n\n2. Click on \"Forgot password?\"\n\n3. Enter your Gmail address\n\n4. Click \"Next\"\n\n5. Choose \"Try another way\" if needed\n\n6. Select \"Text message (SMS)\" option\n\n7. Enter the recovery mobile number associated with your account\n\n8. Google will send a 6-digit verification code to your phone\n\n9. Enter the code on the verification screen\n\n10. Create a new, strong password\n\n11. Click \"Change password\"\n\nAlternative recovery methods:\n- Use a backup email address\n- Answer security questions\n- Use Google's account recovery form\n\nTips:\n- Ensure your recovery phone number is current\n- Have your recovery email address ready\n- Use a unique, strong password\n- Enable two-factor authentication for added security\n\nIf these steps don't work, contact Google Support directly for further assistance.",
